[env] Created frontend_mobile/.env with local LAN API base http://172.19.227.180:8000/api and default map coordinates for local Expo/mobile frontend runs.
[build] Added frontend_mobile EAS build configuration (eas.json), Android/iOS identifiers in app.json, and npm scripts for Expo/EAS dev and Android builds; validated expo config and kept typecheck green.
[fix] Fixed frontend_mobile Babel config: moved nativewind/babel to presets, removed redundant reanimated plugin, and resolved Metro error '.plugins is not a valid Plugin property'; expo config and typecheck are green.
[design] Started web-parity redesign for frontend_mobile: switched shared theme, shell background, header chrome, tab bar, buttons, and inbox action toward the website blue/white app-shell language; typecheck and jest remain green (22 suites / 71 tests).
[design] Rebuilt frontend_mobile LoginScreen as a direct mobile adaptation of the website auth card: centered white auth shell, email/phone segmented tabs, denser input stack, web-like demo accounts box, and simplified auth actions; typecheck and jest remain green (22 suites / 71 tests).
[design] Tightened LoginScreen web-parity pass: replaced text logo with real USC asset, fixed mojibake labels, and introduced auth-specific TextField styling to match the website input look more closely; typecheck and jest remain green (22 suites / 71 tests).
[design] Rebuilt buyer HomeScreen as a direct mobile adaptation of the website home: USC logo row, inline search box, icon category rail, premium banner, and website-like product grid composition; typecheck and jest remain green (22 suites / 71 tests).
[runtime] Started dockerized USC backend stack via existing usc-postgres/usc-redis/usc-backend containers, verified /api/health on port 8001, and updated frontend_mobile/.env API base from :8000 to :8001 for Expo/mobile demo logins.
[ux] Improved global mobile button press feedback in frontend_mobile Buttons: added stronger pressed-state scale/translate, clearer background change, and Android ripple so taps feel distinct from scroll gestures; typecheck and jest remain green (22 suites / 71 tests).
[ux] Strengthened global button press feedback further: noticeably deeper pressed scale/offset plus stronger opacity/background shift, after user reported taps still looked like scroll on device; typecheck and jest remain green (22 suites / 71 tests).
[design] Rebuilt RegisterScreen and ForgotPasswordScreen as direct mobile adaptations of the website auth card: same white auth shell, graphic USC logo, denser website-like input stack, segmented auth method controls, and simplified recovery/registration actions; typecheck and jest remain green (22 suites / 71 tests).
